cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a technique to improve the training of deep neural networks, specifically focusing on the Transformer architecture used in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the application of ReZero to other residual networks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
